headline: Conagra Brands Enters Into a Definitive Agreement with High Liner Foods to Divest the Van de Kamp's® and Mrs. Paul's® Brands
summary: Today Conagra Brands, Inc. (NYSE: CAG) announced that it has entered into a definitive agreement with High Liner Foods to sell its Van de Kamp's® and Mrs. Paul's® frozen seafood brands for $55 million in cash. The transaction includes all associated intellectual property and inventory. The transaction does not include employees or manufacturing facilities. The Van de Kamp's and Mrs. Paul's products that are part of the transaction contributed approximately $75 million to Conagra's fiscal year 20
